  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2024-01-24",
    "date": "2024-03-20T15:45:35Z",
    "text": "Child and Dependent Care Tax Credit Enhancement Act of 2024\n\nThis bill modifies the tax credit for employment-related expenses incurred for the care of a taxpayer's dependent to (1) increase to $400,000, the adjusted gross income threshold level above which the credit is incrementally reduced; (2) increase the dollar limits on the allowable amount of the credit; (3) specify rules for married couples filing separate returns; (4) allow an inflation adjustment to the adjusted gross income threshold and the maximum credit amounts, beginning after 2024; and (5) make the credit refundable for taxpayers who have a principal residence for more than half of the taxable year."
  },
